This paper discusses representation learning, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions feedforward processing in sensory cortex, which is related to neural networks and neuroscience, making cs.NE a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the selectivity of the learned representations, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
